# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The approved Phase 0 documentation set.
#
# These documents were reviewed and approved as they stand. Prettier would
# rewrite all 31 of them — ~500 lines — purely to change `*emphasis*` into
# `_emphasis_` and to re-pad every Markdown table. Neither behavior is
# configurable, and neither changes a single word of content.
#
# Phase 1 does not spend the Phase 0 review on that. A pull request that adds a
# toolchain and also churns the entire approved architecture set is a pull
# request in which the boundary documents cannot be reviewed, because the real
# changes are buried in whitespace. Formatting is not worth obscuring the one
# thing this repository exists to protect.
#
# Exit path: normalize these files in a dedicated, formatting-only pull request
# that changes nothing else, and delete this block in the same change. Until
# then they are exempt from `pnpm format:check` — not from review.
#
# Everything written from Phase 1 onward is Prettier's: README.md,
# docs/engineering/**, ADR-0009 and later, and all code and configuration.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
docs/architecture/
docs/charter/
docs/governance/
docs/decisions/ADR-000[1-8]-*.md
